<Author>travelwith2kids_8
<Content>Great family resort! We just came back from 4 relaxing days at the Arizona Grand Resort. I was looking for a hotel that was family friendly and had a little adult fun too for my husbands birthday weekend. Having booked the resort online through Expedia I wasn't sure what to expect, but all the reviews sounded pretty good. What a surprise to find a beautiful well maintianed resort with a professional and very accomodating staff.We arrived before check in time, with no problem they gave us our room. A valet drove us to our room and helped us with our bags.We then went to the Oasis Water Park which was a fantstic attraction for both my 3 year old and my 11 month old. We spent both Saturday and Sunday at the waterpark. The lazy river was the hi-light for both children. With Seasonal hours the Oasis was closed the rest of the week so my husband golfed the resorts' course on Monday.He is a pretty avid golfer, golfing at least 3 times a month, and he was pleasantly surprised with this challenging course. It had recently been reseeded so the entire course was flawless. Very impressive course!We were at the resort during their off season, so there were very little crowds anywhere we ventured in the resort. The restaurants were great as well. The Rustlers Roost was a hit with my 3 year old since it is decked out with cowboys, a live bull in the front of the restaurant, and a tin slide in which you can enter the dining area. The Rainforest Cafe is down the street from the Resort, and the Resorts Aunt Chiladas Mexican restaurant had wonderful service and great Mexican food.The workout facility was well equiped and readily available to work out in most parts of the day. We did not have a chance to use the spa facilities.Overall, we were pleasantly surprised with the entire resorts', impeccable grounds and efficient staff. We are looking forward to our next stay there. 
