<Content>Never written a review before- had to with this I have never written a review at TripAdvisor before but have looked at others before. I am not a person to complain about hotels- generally am happy with what i select but had to write today because for the first time ever I felt dooped by the internet view of this hotel. We came for spring break after a trip to the Grand Canyon and Sedona for some RELAXATION at the end of our trip. The hotel room itself was your standard center hall interior one room suite, problem is that this hotel is literally on highway 10. We had what was considered a good room in the Camelback side of the hotel but if you want to sit on the balcomy you will see the highway, signs for Dennys and Carls junior and hear the roar of the interstate. (luckily we had one side of Camelback that was not under construction but beware that on half of that part of the hotel, the view would literlly be a construction site with cement mixers). Again, i could deal with this if that were the worst, but it was not. For the week before Easter, the hotel was totally unprepared. The Water park is the attraction yet on two days that we were here, they had to close the Lazy River due to lack of life guards. When asked, the only explanation was that they had trouble getting reliable college students to help. While that may be a good excuse sometimes, when it is the week before Easter and I am paying incredible top doller I find that inexcusable. Many at the resort today felt the same way. General consensus of those who had been to the resort before was that it had been better run before and that they had never had an issue with the main attractions of the hotel beingclosed. . Not sure what the issue is but another example of the resort's inabilty to deal with the number of people they had at the hotel was the fact that for the 4 days we were there, we could not rent a movie in the nightime because of overcapacity ( the term used by the receptiinist when asked why the TV did not work). Again, I have never written any review, but felt so strongly that the internet picture of this hotel in this case is just false. There is no view, there is no management of the hotel that is watching the problems and overall this is not a hotel I would recommend to anyone. 
